ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How easy or difficult do you think this task will be?
Notes: 1= Extremely easy; 2= Very Easy; 3= Somewhat easy; 4= Typical (neither easy, nor difficulty); 5= Somewhat difficult; 6= Very difficult; 7= Extremely difficult

ElementDescription: How easy or difficult do you think that task was?
Notes: 1= Extremely easy; 2= Very Easy; 3= Somewhat easy; 4= Typical (neither easy, nor difficulty); 5= Somewhat difficult; 6= Very difficult; 7= Extremely difficult

ElementDescription: How do you think you performed on that task
Notes: 1= Extremely well; 2= Very well; 3= Somewhat well; 4= Typical (neither well, nor poorly); 5= Somewhat poorly; 6= Very poorly; 7= Extremely poorly

ElementDescription: How much effort did it take you to complete this task
Notes: 1= Extremely low; 2= Very low; 3= Somewhat low; 4= Typical (neither low, nor high); Somewhat high; 6= Very high; 7= Extremely high
